Property Deals Rise in Macao
MACAO , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- Altogether 10,509 property transaction contracts were signed in Macao during the first nine months of 1998 , up 5.5 percent over the same months last year .
According to figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department , the contracts were worth 6.72 billion patacas ( 840 million U.S. dollars ) , down 46.4 percent from the same period of 1997 .
In the third quarter of the year , 3,826 contracts were signed involving 2.39 billion patacas ( 298 million U.S. dollars ) , up 13.1 percent and down 3.5 percent respectively in comparison with the same quarter of 1997 .
About 86.9 percent of property transactions involved residential houses .
Over the past several months , there have been more housing advertisements in newspapers , together with reports saying that the real estate sector has turned for the better and shown a sign of recovery .
